t=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p><a data-keyword=\"true\" href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/games/genshin-impact\">Genshin Impact</a>'s version 5.1 update is not fully voiced in English due to \"recording arrangements\".</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/genshin-impacts-latest-update-isnt-fully-voiced-in-english-due-to-recording-arrangements\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1294391, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/genshin-impacts-latest-update-isnt-fully-voiced-in-english-due-to-recording-arrangements", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 107, "source_url": "https://www.eurogamer.net/feed", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": "https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Genshin-Impact-Kinich-materials%2C-kit%2C-and-Constellations-cover.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp", "title": "Genshin Impact's latest update isn't fully voiced in English due to \"recording arrangements\"", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-09T14:43:19+00:00", "description": "<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/A-Quiet-Place-The-Road-Ahead-header.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>A Quiet Place: The Road Ahead - the <a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/a-quiet-place-the-road-ahead-revealed-for-pc-and-consoles\">upcoming game inspired by the film franchise of the same name</a> - is set to include an optional microphone feature that allows its creatures to detect any real-life noises made by the player.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/a-quiet-place-the-road-ahead-has-a-new-mic-feature-which-makes-the-game-even-more-terrifying\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1294392, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/a-quiet-place-the-road-ahead-has-a-new-mic-feature-which-makes-the-game-even-more-terrifying", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 107, "source_url": "https://www.eurogamer.net/feed", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": "https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/A-Quiet-Place-The-Road-Ahead-header.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp", "title": "A Quiet Place: The Road ahead has a new mic feature which makes the game even more terrifying", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-09T13:58:16+00:00", "description": "<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Nintendo-interactive-alarm-clock-alarmo-on-a-bedside-table.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>Nintendo has today unveiled Alarmo, an interactive alarm clock that will respond to your body's movements by playing video game sounds, thanks to its motion sensor technology.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/nintendo-just-unveiled-an-alarm-clock-that-plays-mario-coin-noises-when-you-roll-over\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1293892, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/nintendo-just-unveiled-an-alarm-clock-that-plays-mario-coin-noises-when-you-roll-over", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 107, "source_url": "https://www.eurogamer.net/feed", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": "https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Nintendo-interactive-alarm-clock-alarmo-on-a-bedside-table.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp", "title": "Nintendo just unveiled an alarm clock that plays Mario coin noises when you roll over", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-09T12:00:47+00:00", "description": "<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Screenshot-2024-10-09-125718.png?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>\nPlayStation has removed <a data-keyword=\"true\" href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/games/hotline-miami\">Hotline Miami</a> 2 from sale in Australia and refunded PS5 owners who bought the game, a decade on from the infamous kerfuffle over its release down under. \n</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/playstation-suddenly-pulls-hotline-miami-2-from-aussie-ps5-owners-after-realising-countrys-ratings-board-denied-games-release-a-decade-ago\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1293437, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/playstation-suddenly-pulls-hotline-miami-2-from-aussie-ps5-owners-after-realising-countrys-ratings-board-denied-games-release-a-decade-ago", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 107, "source_url": "https://www.eurogamer.net/feed", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": "https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Screenshot-2024-10-09-125718.png?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp", "title": "PlayStation suddenly pulls Hotline Miami 2 from Aussie PS5 owners after realising country's ratings board denied game's release a decade ago", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-09T11:59:17+00:00", "description": "<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/hawthorne-1.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>Yesterday, several former developers from studios such as Bethesda, BioWare and <a data-keyword=\"true\" href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/companies/naughty-dog\">Naughty Dog</a> revealed their upcoming game - the rather delightful looking Hawthorn.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/cosy-rpg-hawthorn-looks-like-stardew-valley-and-skyrim-had-an-adorable-baby-together\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1293041, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/cosy-rpg-hawthorn-looks-like-stardew-valley-and-skyrim-had-an-adorable-baby-together", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 107, "source_url": "https://www.eurogamer.net/feed", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": "https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/hawthorne-1.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp", "title": "Cosy RPG Hawthorn looks like Stardew Valley and Skyrim had an adorable baby together", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-09T11:33:05+00:00", "description": "<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Screenshot-2024-10-09-121823.png?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>\nEx-Humble Games staff made redundant in July have formed a fresh indie publisher, Good Games Group.\n</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/former-humble-games-staff-found-new-indie-publisher\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1293042, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/former-humble-games-staff-found-new-indie-publisher", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 107, "source_url": "https://www.eurogamer.net/feed", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": "https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Screenshot-2024-10-09-121823.png?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp", "title": "Former Humble Games staff found new indie publisher", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-09T11:11:08+00:00", "description": "<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/SILENT-HILL-2-_-Release-Date-Trailer-(4K_EN_ESRB)-_-KONAMI-0-28-screenshot.png?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>PC players are already busy modding <a data-keyword=\"true\" href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/games/silent-hill-2-remake\">Silent Hill 2 Remake</a>, reverting the game to something more akin to the original release.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/silent-hill-2-remake-modders-remove-fog-and-replace-james-sunderland-in-nod-to-hd-collection\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1293043, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/silent-hill-2-remake-modders-remove-fog-and-replace-james-sunderland-in-nod-to-hd-collection", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 107, "source_url": "https://www.eurogamer.net/feed", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": "https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/SILENT-HILL-2-_-Release-Date-Trailer-(4K_EN_ESRB)-_-KONAMI-0-28-screenshot.png?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp", "title": "Silent Hill 2 Remake modders remove fog and replace James Sunderland in nod to HD Collection", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-09T10:52:59+00:00", "description": "<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Red-Dead-Redemption-on-PC.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>We all knew it was coming, but yesterday, after multiple leaks, Rockstar finally announced <a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/red-dead-redemption-coming-to-pc-later-this-month\">Red Dead Redemption will soon launch on PC</a>.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/here-are-red-dead-redemptions-pc-requirements\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1293044, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/here-are-red-dead-redemptions-pc-requirements", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 107, "source_url": "https://www.eurogamer.net/feed", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": "https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Red-Dead-Redemption-on-PC.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp", "title": "Here are Red Dead Redemption's PC requirements", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-09T10:30:11+00:00", "description": "<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/revenge-of-shinobi-cover.png?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>A film adaptation of Sega's Shinobi series is in the works from Universal.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/segas-shinobi-series-next-to-receive-film-adaptation\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1292592, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/segas-shinobi-series-next-to-receive-film-adaptation", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 107, "source_url": "https://www.eurogamer.net/feed", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": "https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/revenge-of-shinobi-cover.png?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp", "title": "Sega's Shinobi series next to receive film adaptation", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-09T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/EG.png?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>\nA fantasy Persona game - that's the back of a napkin pitch for <a data-keyword=\"true\" href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/games/metaphor-refantazio\">Metaphor: ReFantazio</a>, the upcoming Atlus RPG that blends the key mechanics from the Persona games with a novel fantasy setting. But Metaphor marries this with an expanded scope, situating its lengthy story campaign within a semi-open world game structure. That could spell trouble for Atlus, who haven't necessarily been known for technical prowess over recent years - and it's fair to say that for all of the brilliance in the game design, Metaphor: ReFantazio has some profound technical issues at odds with the relative modesty of the visuals.\n</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/digitalfoundry-2024-metaphor-refantazio-a-sublime-game-let-down-by-bizarre-technical-choices\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1292593, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/digitalfoundry-2024-metaphor-refantazio-a-sublime-game-let-down-by-bizarre-technical-choices", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 107, "source_url": "https://www.eurogamer.net/feed", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": "https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/EG.png?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp", "title": "Metaphor: ReFantazio - a sublime game let down by bizarre technical choices", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-09T09:58:04+00:00", "description": "<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Like-A-Dragon-Pirate-Yakuza-in-Hawaii-protagonist-Goro-Majima.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>Once upon a time, Ryu Ga Gotoku Studio toyed with calling its upcoming spin-off Pirate Yakuza in Hawaii 'Like A Dragon: Tuna', with the idea to have the series' original protagonist Kazuma Kiryu star as a fighting fisherman.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/pirate-yakuza-in-hawaii-began-life-as-like-a-dragon-tuna-and-featured-kazuma-kiryu-as-a-fighting-fisherman\">Read more</a></p>", "id": 1292594, "language": "en-gb", "link": "https://www.eurogamer.net/pirate-yakuza-i